1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,420
 (soft music)

2
00:00:02,420 --> 00:00:20,440
 - All right, well, Porch, how are we doing tonight?

3
00:00:20,440 --> 00:00:21,440
 We're doing okay?

4
00:00:21,440 --> 00:00:22,360
 (audience cheering)

5
00:00:22,360 --> 00:00:23,680
 Let's go.

6
00:00:23,680 --> 00:00:25,880
 Oh my gosh.

7
00:00:25,880 --> 00:00:27,880
 I cannot tell you how long I have been waiting

8
00:00:27,880 --> 00:00:30,760
 to say those very words to this room.

9
00:00:30,760 --> 00:00:32,040
 I have missed you.

10
00:00:32,040 --> 00:00:36,140
 Like, I don't know if that feeling is reciprocal,

11
00:00:36,140 --> 00:00:38,800
 but you need to know at least one person in this world

12
00:00:38,800 --> 00:00:40,280
 has missed you, and it is me.

13
00:00:40,280 --> 00:00:42,580
 I'm so glad you're here.

14
00:00:42,580 --> 00:00:45,780
 If you're a faithful friend to the Porch,

15
00:00:45,780 --> 00:00:47,400
 if you're with us regularly,

16
00:00:47,400 --> 00:00:49,080
 if this is something that you're a part of,

17
00:00:49,080 --> 00:00:51,400
 Tuesday after Tuesday, welcome back.

18
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:52,440
 It's so good to see you.

19
00:00:52,440 --> 00:00:53,920
 I'm so glad you're here.

20
00:00:53,920 --> 00:00:55,560
 And then if you're new to the room, you know,

21
00:00:55,560 --> 00:00:56,760
 like if this is your first time,

22
00:00:56,760 --> 00:00:58,800
 I don't know how you got drug in here

23
00:00:58,800 --> 00:01:00,880
 or duped into joining us,

24
00:01:00,880 --> 00:01:03,400
 but I'm so glad you're here as well.

25
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:04,840
 I said this at the beginning of the night,

26
00:01:04,840 --> 00:01:05,760
 but I just want to reiterate it

27
00:01:05,760 --> 00:01:08,280
 'cause I think it matters so much for you to understand.

28
00:01:08,280 --> 00:01:11,480
 I truly, in my heart of hearts,

29
00:01:11,480 --> 00:01:14,220
 I'm not just trying to sell you a bill of goods.

30
00:01:14,220 --> 00:01:18,060
 I think, I believe, I expect

31
00:01:18,060 --> 00:01:20,840
 that God wants to move in your life,

32
00:01:20,840 --> 00:01:23,060
 that He wants to meet with you,

33
00:01:23,060 --> 00:01:25,140
 that His plans for your life,

34
00:01:25,140 --> 00:01:28,340
 they're better than any plans you have for yourself.

35
00:01:28,340 --> 00:01:31,720
 And so tonight, I just want to encourage you.

36
00:01:31,720 --> 00:01:35,380
 Come on, like, let's go see what the Lord has to say

37
00:01:35,380 --> 00:01:38,720
 here at the beginning of a brand new year.

38
00:01:38,720 --> 00:01:42,440
 Now, I would be remiss if I didn't just say hello

39
00:01:42,440 --> 00:01:43,760
 to everybody else that's tuning in online

40
00:01:43,760 --> 00:01:47,700
 because while we've got a packed house here in Dallas, Texas,

41
00:01:47,700 --> 00:01:49,400
 we've also got so many people

42
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:51,520
 tuning in online with us right now.

43
00:01:51,520 --> 00:01:56,060
 And so everybody out there, Porch Live, like, welcome.

44
00:01:56,060 --> 00:01:58,380
 It's so good to be back together with you.

45
00:01:58,380 --> 00:02:00,220
 And we're really expecting

46
00:02:00,220 --> 00:02:01,500
 that God isn't just going to move here,

47
00:02:01,500 --> 00:02:02,660
 He's going to move there too.

48
00:02:02,660 --> 00:02:03,480
 We believe it.

49
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:05,580
 I've said it, and I'm going to say it again.

50
00:02:05,580 --> 00:02:08,120
 God can meet with any person, anytime, in any place,

51
00:02:08,120 --> 00:02:10,220
 and that includes you.

52
00:02:10,220 --> 00:02:13,340
 Special shout out to Porch Live, Fort Worth,

53
00:02:13,340 --> 00:02:16,500
 Midland, Springfield, Greater Lafayette,

54
00:02:16,500 --> 00:02:20,820
 Boise, Scottsdale, Wheaton, Dayton, and Fresno.

55
00:02:20,820 --> 00:02:23,120
 Hey, Dallas, can we put our hands together

56
00:02:23,120 --> 00:02:25,280
 for all of our Porch Live locations?

57
00:02:25,280 --> 00:02:26,120
 Amazing.

58
00:02:26,120 --> 00:02:27,380
 We love you guys so much.

59
00:02:27,380 --> 00:02:30,180
 Hey, here's what I want to do.

60
00:02:30,180 --> 00:02:31,320
 If you have a copy of the scriptures,

61
00:02:31,320 --> 00:02:32,920
 would you go ahead and grab it?

62
00:02:32,920 --> 00:02:36,480
 Would you turn with me to that first page of your Bible,

63
00:02:36,480 --> 00:02:38,480
 Genesis chapter one?

64
00:02:38,480 --> 00:02:40,880
 Normally, I try to give you some time

65
00:02:40,880 --> 00:02:43,200
 to get to whatever book we're going to be reading,

66
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:44,040
 but this one's easy.

67
00:02:44,040 --> 00:02:47,280
 You just got to flip a couple of pages and you're there.

68
00:02:47,280 --> 00:02:48,640
 If you don't have a copy of the scriptures,

69
00:02:48,640 --> 00:02:49,540
 here's what I would just tell you.

70
00:02:49,540 --> 00:02:51,220
 We would love to give you one.

71
00:02:51,220 --> 00:02:54,040
 We want every single person to have this book

72
00:02:54,040 --> 00:02:55,960
 sitting in their lap as they gather with us

73
00:02:55,960 --> 00:02:56,840
 here on Tuesday nights.

74
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:58,760
 We, of course, will always have it behind us,

75
00:02:58,760 --> 00:03:01,880
 and that's a useful tool if you don't have a copy

76
00:03:01,880 --> 00:03:02,760
 or you forget your copy,

77
00:03:02,760 --> 00:03:05,160
 but we would love to make sure that you have one.

78
00:03:05,160 --> 00:03:07,960
 So step outside, visit with our welcome desk.

79
00:03:07,960 --> 00:03:10,320
 They would love to give you a copy of the Bible.

80
00:03:10,320 --> 00:03:12,100
 But here is Genesis chapter one.

81
00:03:12,100 --> 00:03:13,360
 I'll say this.

82
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:16,600
 We're not going to read the entire chapter.

83
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:19,120
 I know.

84
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:20,460
 But here's what I would say to you, sir.

85
00:03:20,460 --> 00:03:21,920
 You can do that yourself.

86
00:03:21,920 --> 00:03:25,360
 There's 34 verses that we're going to look at

87
00:03:25,360 --> 00:03:27,140
 between chapter one and then a few verses

88
00:03:27,140 --> 00:03:28,440
 at the top of chapter two.

89
00:03:28,440 --> 00:03:31,460
 I'm going to read a lot of it for us,

90
00:03:31,460 --> 00:03:34,180
 but I'm hoping that it just helps us to catch the rhythm

91
00:03:34,180 --> 00:03:36,820
 of what's happening in this text.

92
00:03:36,820 --> 00:03:38,360
 So here's what it says.

93
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:39,260
 Genesis one.

94
00:03:39,260 --> 00:03:42,960
 It says, "In the beginning,

95
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:45,720
 God created the heavens and the earth.

96
00:03:45,720 --> 00:03:49,420
 The earth was without form and void.

97
00:03:49,420 --> 00:03:52,000
 And darkness was over the face of the deep.

98
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:53,780
 And the spirit of God was hovering

99
00:03:53,780 --> 00:03:56,060
 over the face of the waters.

100
00:03:56,060 --> 00:03:58,900
 And God said, 'Let there be light.'

101
00:03:58,900 --> 00:04:00,400
 And there was light.

102
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:02,620
 And God saw that the light was good.

103
00:04:02,620 --> 00:04:05,540
 And God separated the light from the darkness.

104
00:04:05,540 --> 00:04:07,180
 God had called the light day,

105
00:04:07,180 --> 00:04:09,460
 and the darkness he called night.

106
00:04:09,460 --> 00:04:11,820
 And there was evening, and there was morning,

107
00:04:11,820 --> 00:04:13,280
 the first day.

108
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:15,680
 And God said, 'Let there be an expanse

109
00:04:15,680 --> 00:04:16,700
 in the midst of the waters,

110
00:04:16,700 --> 00:04:19,100
 and let it separate the waters from the waters.'

111
00:04:19,100 --> 00:04:21,300
 And God made the expanse and separated the waters

112
00:04:21,300 --> 00:04:23,700
 that were under the expanse from the waters

113
00:04:23,700 --> 00:04:25,740
 that were above the expanse.

114
00:04:25,740 --> 00:04:27,060
 And it was so.

115
00:04:27,060 --> 00:04:29,060
 And God called the expanse heaven.

116
00:04:29,060 --> 00:04:31,420
 And there was evening, and there was morning,

117
00:04:31,420 --> 00:04:32,400
 the second day."

118
00:04:32,400 --> 00:04:35,260
 We're going to jump down now,

119
00:04:35,260 --> 00:04:36,780
 but if you were to keep reading,

120
00:04:36,780 --> 00:04:39,040
 you would see God's creation of day three,

121
00:04:39,040 --> 00:04:41,800
 where he separates the waters from the land.

122
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:42,900
 You would see day four,

123
00:04:42,900 --> 00:04:46,660
 where he casts the sun, moon, and stars into the heavens.

124
00:04:46,660 --> 00:04:50,160
 You would see day five,

125
00:04:50,160 --> 00:04:53,740
 where God, he brings fish and birds,

126
00:04:53,740 --> 00:04:56,860
 fish to swim in the sea, birds to fly in the sky.

127
00:04:56,860 --> 00:04:59,740
 And then he brings on day six, this.

128
00:04:59,740 --> 00:05:04,340
 And God said, verse 24,

129
00:05:04,340 --> 00:05:06,640
 "Let the earth bring forth living creatures

130
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:10,100
 according to their kinds, livestock, creeping things,

131
00:05:10,100 --> 00:05:12,480
 and beasts of the earth according to their kinds.

132
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:14,180
 And it was so.

133
00:05:14,180 --> 00:05:15,640
 And God made the beasts of the earth

134
00:05:15,640 --> 00:05:16,560
 according to their kinds,

135
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:17,860
 and livestock according to their kinds,

136
00:05:17,860 --> 00:05:19,060
 and everything that creeps in the ground

137
00:05:19,060 --> 00:05:19,900
 according to its kind.

138
00:05:19,900 --> 00:05:22,200
 And God saw that it was good.

139
00:05:22,200 --> 00:05:25,220
 Then God said,

140
00:05:25,220 --> 00:05:29,360
 "Let us make man in our image, after our likeness,

141
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:32,260
 and let them have dominion over the fish of the sea,

142
00:05:32,260 --> 00:05:33,700
 and over the birds of the heavens,

143
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:36,300
 and over the livestock, and over all the earth,

144
00:05:36,300 --> 00:05:39,140
 and over every creeping thing that creeps on the earth."

145
00:05:40,340 --> 00:05:43,480
 So God created man in his own image.

146
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:44,980
 In the image of God, he created him.

147
00:05:44,980 --> 00:05:46,560
 Male and female, he created them.

148
00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:47,440
 And God blessed them.

149
00:05:47,440 --> 00:05:48,360
 And God said to them,

150
00:05:48,360 --> 00:05:50,480
 "Be fruitful and multiply.

151
00:05:50,480 --> 00:05:51,760
 Fill the earth and subdue it,

152
00:05:51,760 --> 00:05:53,320
 and have dominion over the fish of the sea,

153
00:05:53,320 --> 00:05:54,760
 and over the birds of the heavens,

154
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:57,260
 and over every living thing that moves on the earth."

155
00:05:57,260 --> 00:05:59,680
 And God said, "Behold,

156
00:05:59,680 --> 00:06:01,960
 I've given you every plant yielding seed

157
00:06:01,960 --> 00:06:05,000
 that is on the face of all the earth,

158
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:06,880
 and every tree with seed in its fruit.

159
00:06:06,880 --> 00:06:08,480
 You shall have them for food.

160
00:06:08,480 --> 00:06:10,580
 And every beast of the earth,

161
00:06:10,580 --> 00:06:11,800
 and every bird of the heavens,

162
00:06:11,800 --> 00:06:13,260
 and everything that creeps on the earth,

163
00:06:13,260 --> 00:06:17,140
 everything that has the breath of life,

164
00:06:17,140 --> 00:06:19,900
 I have given every green plant for food."

165
00:06:19,900 --> 00:06:21,340
 And it was so.

166
00:06:21,340 --> 00:06:24,400
 And God saw everything that he made,

167
00:06:24,400 --> 00:06:27,740
 and behold, it was very good.

168
00:06:27,740 --> 00:06:29,140
 And there was evening, and there was morning.

169
00:06:29,140 --> 00:06:32,380
 The sixth day, chapter two,

170
00:06:32,380 --> 00:06:35,100
 "Thus the heavens and the earth were finished,

171
00:06:35,100 --> 00:06:36,500
 and all the host of them.

172
00:06:36,500 --> 00:06:38,840
 And on the seventh day, God finished his work

173
00:06:38,840 --> 00:06:40,720
 that he had done, and he rested on the seventh day

174
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:41,960
 from all his work that he had done,

175
00:06:41,960 --> 00:06:44,980
 and God blessed the seventh day, and he made it holy,

176
00:06:44,980 --> 00:06:47,480
 because on it, God rested from all his work

177
00:06:47,480 --> 00:06:48,940
 that he had done in creation."

178
00:06:48,940 --> 00:06:50,520
 Let me pray for us.

179
00:06:50,520 --> 00:06:55,380
 God, this is your holy word.

180
00:06:55,380 --> 00:07:00,380
 It's so much more than black print on a piece of paper.

181
00:07:00,380 --> 00:07:04,280
 God, this is your word.

182
00:07:04,280 --> 00:07:08,020
 You have spoken this, God, from times past

183
00:07:08,020 --> 00:07:10,420
 into times present, so that way, God,

184
00:07:10,420 --> 00:07:12,000
 it wouldn't just fill our minds,

185
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:15,060
 it would change our hearts.

186
00:07:15,060 --> 00:07:16,940
 It would shape us, God,

187
00:07:16,940 --> 00:07:19,340
 into becoming who you want us to be.

188
00:07:19,340 --> 00:07:23,180
 And so, God, I pray you would do that right now.

189
00:07:23,180 --> 00:07:27,160
 God, here in this room, we need you.

190
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:30,320
 You, Jesus, have supplied our every need

191
00:07:30,320 --> 00:07:32,680
 by way of your life, death, and resurrection.

192
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:34,740
 And God, also, we want you,

193
00:07:34,740 --> 00:07:37,700
 because we know Christ, there is none like you.

194
00:07:37,700 --> 00:07:39,420
 Won't you meet with us now, we pray,

195
00:07:39,420 --> 00:07:41,240
 in Christ's name, amen.

196
00:07:41,240 --> 00:07:46,860
 Well, I remember when I was 25 years old,

197
00:07:46,860 --> 00:07:51,460
 I experienced my very own personal quarter-life crisis.

198
00:07:51,460 --> 00:07:54,660
 At the time, I didn't know

199
00:07:54,660 --> 00:07:56,300
 that it's actually what I was going through,

200
00:07:56,300 --> 00:07:58,800
 but now, looking back, I can identify it clearly.

201
00:07:58,800 --> 00:08:00,420
 The reason why I didn't know, though, at the time,

202
00:08:00,420 --> 00:08:01,740
 that that's what I was actually experiencing

203
00:08:01,740 --> 00:08:03,860
 was because it didn't look like what I expected.

204
00:08:03,860 --> 00:08:05,960
 It wasn't the alarm clock

205
00:08:05,960 --> 00:08:08,940
 of some personal panic going off in my life.

206
00:08:08,940 --> 00:08:11,360
 It wasn't that my pillow was drenched

207
00:08:11,360 --> 00:08:13,480
 with the tears of all of my existential dread.

208
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:15,380
 No, in fact, I didn't realize

209
00:08:15,380 --> 00:08:16,940
 that I was going through a quarter-life crisis,

210
00:08:16,940 --> 00:08:18,820
 because at that time, I was, well,

211
00:08:18,820 --> 00:08:20,860
 I was doing a lot of stuff, you know?

212
00:08:20,860 --> 00:08:23,700
 In that time of my life, I had just changed companies.

213
00:08:23,700 --> 00:08:27,740
 I had moved out of one company into this tech startup,

214
00:08:27,740 --> 00:08:29,780
 and this tech startup was up and coming.

215
00:08:29,780 --> 00:08:31,820
 They had so much promise and potential.

216
00:08:31,820 --> 00:08:34,620
 They were getting looks from the rest of the industry,

217
00:08:34,620 --> 00:08:36,860
 and it was super exciting.

218
00:08:36,860 --> 00:08:37,940
 And at the same time,

219
00:08:37,940 --> 00:08:42,140
 I had jumped into this residency with my local church.

220
00:08:42,140 --> 00:08:44,460
 They were trying to get people in

221
00:08:44,460 --> 00:08:45,900
 to gain some practical experience,

222
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:46,720
 and I thought, man, you know what?

223
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:48,780
 I think that I might wanna go into ministry one day,

224
00:08:48,780 --> 00:08:49,740
 and so let me hop into that

225
00:08:49,740 --> 00:08:51,180
 and get some experience while I'm at it.

226
00:08:51,180 --> 00:08:53,140
 And simultaneous to that, I also knew,

227
00:08:53,140 --> 00:08:54,620
 man, I need to begin to learn

228
00:08:54,620 --> 00:08:56,180
 some of the things about the scripture

229
00:08:56,180 --> 00:08:58,180
 if I am going to go into ministry one day.

230
00:08:58,180 --> 00:09:00,820
 So I started taking seminary classes online at night.

231
00:09:00,820 --> 00:09:02,780
 I was working in the day, and I was doing residency stuff

232
00:09:02,780 --> 00:09:04,100
 whenever I could sneak away at lunches

233
00:09:04,100 --> 00:09:05,900
 and early in the mornings, and then I would come home,

234
00:09:05,900 --> 00:09:08,540
 and I would do seminary late into the evening.

235
00:09:08,540 --> 00:09:10,180
 And then adjacent to that,

236
00:09:10,180 --> 00:09:13,300
 I was also kind of standing up this college ministry

237
00:09:13,300 --> 00:09:14,460
 that had not existed,

238
00:09:14,460 --> 00:09:16,340
 but there were a bunch of college kids gathering around,

239
00:09:16,340 --> 00:09:17,540
 and somebody needed to serve them.

240
00:09:17,540 --> 00:09:19,460
 And I felt like, you know what?

241
00:09:19,460 --> 00:09:20,280
 Why not me?

242
00:09:20,280 --> 00:09:21,120
 Let me jump in.

243
00:09:21,120 --> 00:09:21,940
 I wanna teach.

244
00:09:21,940 --> 00:09:22,780
 This is a good chance for me to teach.

245
00:09:22,780 --> 00:09:23,980
 And also alongside all that,

246
00:09:23,980 --> 00:09:25,460
 I was a part of a sermon prep team

247
00:09:25,460 --> 00:09:29,380
 for a local pastor whom I highly respected.

248
00:09:29,380 --> 00:09:31,900
 And I thought, man, if I can learn a thing or two from him,

249
00:09:31,900 --> 00:09:35,060
 then that's only going to help me further in the future.

250
00:09:35,060 --> 00:09:38,780
 You see, I had so much going on in my life.

251
00:09:38,780 --> 00:09:41,060
 And so one day I'm sitting at lunch

252
00:09:41,060 --> 00:09:44,620
 with none other than Timothy T.A. Atik.

253
00:09:44,620 --> 00:09:45,540
 If you don't know T.A.,

254
00:09:45,540 --> 00:09:47,140
 T.A. is the lead pastor here

255
00:09:47,140 --> 00:09:48,460
 at Watermark Community Church.

256
00:09:48,460 --> 00:09:51,860
 And he's just asking me good conversational questions.

257
00:09:51,860 --> 00:09:53,240
 Hey, man, like what's going on?

258
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:54,080
 What's new in life?

259
00:09:54,080 --> 00:09:54,900
 What are you up to?

260
00:09:54,900 --> 00:09:56,580
 What do you wanna be up to one day?

261
00:09:56,580 --> 00:10:00,140
 And I just go through that whole list with him

262
00:10:00,140 --> 00:10:01,960
 as like some kind of badge of honor, you know,

263
00:10:01,960 --> 00:10:04,100
 because the more you do, the better you are.

264
00:10:04,100 --> 00:10:06,380
 And I unrolled all of it to him.

265
00:10:06,380 --> 00:10:08,540
 And yet what I don't see on his face,

266
00:10:08,540 --> 00:10:11,340
 I don't see that he's impressed.

267
00:10:11,340 --> 00:10:13,100
 In fact, I see that he's surprised.

268
00:10:13,100 --> 00:10:15,620
 He is staring across the table from me at Chipotle,

269
00:10:15,620 --> 00:10:20,620
 fork frozen in hand above his bowl.

270
00:10:20,620 --> 00:10:22,800
 And then he says these words,

271
00:10:23,740 --> 00:10:25,880
 "Bro, what are you doing?"

272
00:10:25,880 --> 00:10:30,800
 To which I replied, "I have no idea."

273
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:34,980
 Cube moment of quarter life crisis.

274
00:10:34,980 --> 00:10:37,660
 Like I realized there and then that, man,

275
00:10:37,660 --> 00:10:41,220
 I was doing so much with my life,

276
00:10:41,220 --> 00:10:43,740
 but I wasn't doing anything in my life.

277
00:10:43,740 --> 00:10:45,020
 Does that make sense to you?

278
00:10:45,020 --> 00:10:48,500
 Like I found myself not experiencing the crisis

279
00:10:48,500 --> 00:10:49,580
 of some kind of panic.

280
00:10:49,580 --> 00:10:53,300
 I found myself experiencing the crisis of over commitment.

281
00:10:53,300 --> 00:10:56,340
 I had no idea what I was doing.

282
00:10:56,340 --> 00:10:59,900
 I had so much activity, but I had zero direction

283
00:10:59,900 --> 00:11:02,820
 because I did not know what my purpose was.

284
00:11:02,820 --> 00:11:04,580
 You ever been in a place like that?

285
00:11:04,580 --> 00:11:08,940
 Where you look up and you realize

286
00:11:08,940 --> 00:11:11,760
 you don't have a clue what you're doing.

287
00:11:11,760 --> 00:11:14,520
 That tends to be a pretty pervasive thought

288
00:11:14,520 --> 00:11:15,780
 around this time of year.

289
00:11:15,780 --> 00:11:18,300
 Whenever you kind of move out of the old year

290
00:11:18,300 --> 00:11:19,780
 and into the new year,

291
00:11:19,780 --> 00:11:22,780
 what happens is you're prompted to reflect

292
00:11:22,780 --> 00:11:24,260
 on everything that happened in the past

293
00:11:24,260 --> 00:11:25,420
 and you're provoked to consider

294
00:11:25,420 --> 00:11:26,700
 what you'll resolve for the future.

295
00:11:26,700 --> 00:11:28,740
 And as you do all of that,

296
00:11:28,740 --> 00:11:31,740
 these questions of what am I doing begin to surface.

297
00:11:31,740 --> 00:11:33,380
 If you've ever thought most resolutions

298
00:11:33,380 --> 00:11:35,060
 are the product of regret, right?

299
00:11:35,060 --> 00:11:37,340
 Like what am I doing with my health?

300
00:11:37,340 --> 00:11:38,660
 Like my doctor said I shouldn't,

301
00:11:38,660 --> 00:11:40,120
 but I keep going and doing,

302
00:11:40,120 --> 00:11:42,500
 or what am I doing in this job that I hate?

303
00:11:42,500 --> 00:11:43,580
 Like, why didn't I change that?

304
00:11:43,580 --> 00:11:45,020
 Or what am I doing in this relationship

305
00:11:45,020 --> 00:11:47,060
 that I know it ain't going the distance?

306
00:11:47,060 --> 00:11:48,020
 This isn't marriage material.

307
00:11:48,020 --> 00:11:51,260
 Or what am I doing with my money?

308
00:11:51,260 --> 00:11:54,540
 It's supposed to be piling up.

309
00:11:54,540 --> 00:11:56,080
 Instead, it is emptying out.

310
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:58,060
 I'm spending more than I'm actually saving.

311
00:11:58,060 --> 00:12:00,980
 What am I doing with my life?

312
00:12:00,980 --> 00:12:03,700
 That's what often happens at this time of year.

313
00:12:03,700 --> 00:12:05,420
 At the beginning of 2026,

314
00:12:05,420 --> 00:12:08,740
 you're probably facing a wake-up call.

315
00:12:08,740 --> 00:12:10,980
 Maybe it's even a gut punch

316
00:12:10,980 --> 00:12:13,580
 because you've been forced to stare at yourself

317
00:12:13,580 --> 00:12:15,860
 and take a good hard look in the mirror

318
00:12:15,860 --> 00:12:17,980
 and ask the question,

319
00:12:17,980 --> 00:12:20,920
 what purpose am I actually pursuing in life?

320
00:12:20,920 --> 00:12:27,660
 Which in our world can bring about a variety of answers.

321
00:12:27,660 --> 00:12:31,200
 According to naturalism, you don't have to have a purpose.

322
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:32,860
 In fact, you're an accident.

323
00:12:32,860 --> 00:12:34,560
 Really compelling sales pitch.

324
00:12:34,560 --> 00:12:36,640
 The random result of a series of natural processes

325
00:12:36,640 --> 00:12:38,500
 like evolution and natural selection.

326
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:40,260
 According to a new age,

327
00:12:40,260 --> 00:12:43,620
 your purpose is to wake up from your own spiritual amnesia.

328
00:12:43,620 --> 00:12:44,940
 Do you know that's happening to you?

329
00:12:44,940 --> 00:12:48,020
 And raise your vibrational energy.

330
00:12:48,020 --> 00:12:48,900
 Don't know what that means.

331
00:12:48,900 --> 00:12:50,580
 According to most Eastern religions,

332
00:12:50,580 --> 00:12:52,820
 you're stuck in a spiritual spin cycle.

333
00:12:52,820 --> 00:12:56,500
 So your purpose in life is to transcend

334
00:12:56,500 --> 00:12:58,740
 into a higher spiritual state.

335
00:12:58,740 --> 00:13:00,540
 That way you can be liberated from the world.

336
00:13:00,540 --> 00:13:03,820
 You know, according to most Westernized religions,

337
00:13:03,820 --> 00:13:06,820
 your purpose is to pull yourself together

338
00:13:06,820 --> 00:13:07,860
 and get yourself right.

339
00:13:07,860 --> 00:13:11,620
 And according to philosophy, you have no defined purpose.

340
00:13:11,620 --> 00:13:13,400
 You've got to figure that out for yourself.

341
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:18,400
 The world has no shortage of purposes to offer you.

342
00:13:18,400 --> 00:13:25,460
 But God, God has one purpose for your life.

343
00:13:25,460 --> 00:13:28,380
 And it's to know him.

344
00:13:28,380 --> 00:13:30,580
 It's to know him.

345
00:13:30,580 --> 00:13:34,460
 Not like that distant relative that you know,

346
00:13:34,460 --> 00:13:35,920
 that you see once or twice a year.

347
00:13:35,920 --> 00:13:40,180
 And not like that social media or podcast influencer

348
00:13:40,180 --> 00:13:42,140
 that you know all sorts of things about.

349
00:13:42,140 --> 00:13:44,140
 You know every detail of their life.

350
00:13:44,140 --> 00:13:45,380
 You've stored it up in here.

351
00:13:45,380 --> 00:13:47,740
 And yet you've never actually engaged with that person

352
00:13:47,740 --> 00:13:49,840
 nor built any kind of meaningful relationship.

353
00:13:49,840 --> 00:13:50,900
 That's not what we're talking about.

354
00:13:50,900 --> 00:13:52,140
 God wants you to know him.

355
00:13:52,140 --> 00:13:53,380
 He wants you to know him deeply.

356
00:13:53,380 --> 00:13:54,620
 He wants you to know him intimately.

357
00:13:54,620 --> 00:13:56,380
 He wants you to know him personally.

358
00:13:56,380 --> 00:13:59,640
 He wants to bring you into a relationship

359
00:13:59,640 --> 00:14:01,420
 the likes of which you have never before experienced

360
00:14:01,420 --> 00:14:02,980
 and you never will experience.

361
00:14:02,980 --> 00:14:06,140
 Again, that's what God is asking you to do.

362
00:14:06,140 --> 00:14:07,660
 He wants you to know him.

363
00:14:07,660 --> 00:14:10,340
 And so here at the beginning of a brand new year,

364
00:14:10,340 --> 00:14:13,900
 a fresh start, I want to help you do it.

365
00:14:13,900 --> 00:14:15,380
 I want to help you know him.

366
00:14:15,380 --> 00:14:18,420
 I want to help you rediscover your purpose.

367
00:14:18,420 --> 00:14:21,740
 And part of that means I want to reintroduce you

368
00:14:21,740 --> 00:14:23,740
 to the God of the universe.

369
00:14:23,740 --> 00:14:25,060
 Whether you've never met him,

370
00:14:25,060 --> 00:14:26,860
 whether you and him have fallen out

371
00:14:26,860 --> 00:14:27,740
 at some point in their past,

372
00:14:27,740 --> 00:14:29,300
 or whether, and maybe you know him,

373
00:14:29,300 --> 00:14:30,740
 but you want to know him more.

374
00:14:30,740 --> 00:14:33,620
 I think there's no greater study for us

375
00:14:33,620 --> 00:14:34,820
 here at the beginning of a year

376
00:14:34,820 --> 00:14:36,500
 than to say, God, who are you?

377
00:14:36,500 --> 00:14:38,500
 Because at the turn of the year,

378
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:41,260
 so many people, they're thinking about who am I?

379
00:14:41,260 --> 00:14:47,500
 Listen, I am determines who I am.

380
00:14:47,500 --> 00:14:53,700
 If you know him, then I promise you will know you.

381
00:14:53,700 --> 00:14:54,860
 So who is he?

382
00:14:54,860 --> 00:14:59,860
 Well, fortunately, that purpose for which he's designed you

383
00:14:59,860 --> 00:15:03,820
 is something he begins to inform very early in the scripture,

384
00:15:03,820 --> 00:15:05,780
 specifically from the very first page of the Bible.

385
00:15:05,780 --> 00:15:08,340
 He doesn't waste any time helping you get to know him.

386
00:15:08,340 --> 00:15:11,420
 That's why we just read through Genesis chapter one.

387
00:15:11,420 --> 00:15:13,660
 What you see over the course of Genesis

388
00:15:13,660 --> 00:15:18,660
 is God explaining to us, expressing to us who he is.

389
00:15:18,660 --> 00:15:22,100
 Now, Genesis is 50 chapters.

390
00:15:22,100 --> 00:15:24,100
 And as we start this series,

391
00:15:24,100 --> 00:15:26,580
 we're not going to be able to read all 50 chapters.

392
00:15:26,580 --> 00:15:27,500
 If you've ever been in this room

393
00:15:27,500 --> 00:15:29,220
 and you've listened to me preach,

394
00:15:29,220 --> 00:15:32,020
 then you know that is completely impossible.

395
00:15:32,020 --> 00:15:34,060
 We don't have time this year to do that.

396
00:15:34,060 --> 00:15:37,180
 And yet what I do think can help us to know God more

397
00:15:37,180 --> 00:15:42,180
 is to look at 10 portraits through 10 weeks of time

398
00:15:42,180 --> 00:15:46,100
 about who God is specifically.

399
00:15:46,100 --> 00:15:47,500
 Why 10 portraits?

400
00:15:47,500 --> 00:15:50,220
 Well, if I wanted to get to know you and I asked you,

401
00:15:50,220 --> 00:15:53,620
 "Hey, would you grab the 10 most meaningful pictures

402
00:15:53,620 --> 00:15:54,460
 from your life?"

403
00:15:54,460 --> 00:15:56,380
 Chances are I'm going to get a pretty good idea

404
00:15:56,380 --> 00:15:58,820
 of who you are if you walk me through and explain to me

405
00:15:58,820 --> 00:16:00,180
 what each of those photos represent.

406
00:16:00,180 --> 00:16:03,420
 No, the same will be true of God.

407
00:16:03,420 --> 00:16:04,700
 He is inexhaustible.

408
00:16:04,700 --> 00:16:07,820
 We cannot learn him completely at any point in history.

409
00:16:07,820 --> 00:16:10,620
 And yet these portraits will help us to get a good idea

410
00:16:10,620 --> 00:16:12,660
 of who he is nonetheless.

411
00:16:12,660 --> 00:16:18,940
 And what we find is that if we're going to begin to know him

412
00:16:18,940 --> 00:16:21,200
 we should begin with the beginning.

413
00:16:21,200 --> 00:16:22,500
 We should start at chapter one.

414
00:16:22,500 --> 00:16:26,020
 We read it all because we're not necessarily going to look

415
00:16:26,020 --> 00:16:26,900
 at verse by verse by verse.

416
00:16:26,900 --> 00:16:28,820
 We're going to check some key elements

417
00:16:28,820 --> 00:16:31,640
 that kind of weave through this passage,

418
00:16:31,640 --> 00:16:33,260
 but we will just pick it up in verse one.

419
00:16:33,260 --> 00:16:34,100
 Does that sound good?

420
00:16:34,100 --> 00:16:35,380
 So here's what it says in verse one.

421
00:16:35,380 --> 00:16:36,700
 It says, "In the beginning,

422
00:16:36,700 --> 00:16:39,220
 God created the heavens and the earth."

423
00:16:39,220 --> 00:16:41,580
 Now let's just stop there real quick

424
00:16:41,580 --> 00:16:45,340
 because even only this far,

425
00:16:45,340 --> 00:16:50,340
 it is so common in our westernized post-enlightenment mind

426
00:16:50,340 --> 00:16:52,580
 to begin to question, here we go,

427
00:16:52,580 --> 00:16:54,260
 "How's all of it work, Kylan?

428
00:16:54,260 --> 00:16:55,620
 Why don't you tell me, man?

429
00:16:55,620 --> 00:16:56,440
 Let's get into it.

430
00:16:56,440 --> 00:16:58,260
 How old is the age of the earth?

431
00:16:58,260 --> 00:17:02,220
 How is it that humans came to be?

432
00:17:02,220 --> 00:17:03,780
 How is it that the dinosaurs went extinct?

433
00:17:03,780 --> 00:17:05,260
 Tell me, Kylan, I want to know."

434
00:17:05,260 --> 00:17:06,840
 That's not what we're going to be doing here

435
00:17:06,840 --> 00:17:08,220
 because what you need to understand

436
00:17:08,220 --> 00:17:12,420
 is the Bible is not written principally for that purpose.

437
00:17:12,420 --> 00:17:16,100
 Genesis is not filled with scientific intent.

438
00:17:16,100 --> 00:17:18,060
 It is filled with theological intent.

439
00:17:18,060 --> 00:17:21,340
 The Bible is not an instruction manual

440
00:17:21,340 --> 00:17:22,460
 to answer all your questions.

441
00:17:22,460 --> 00:17:26,480
 It is a worship manual to teach you how to engage with God.

442
00:17:26,480 --> 00:17:27,980
 And so as we read through Genesis,

443
00:17:27,980 --> 00:17:30,820
 it's not going to answer the questions of what and how.

444
00:17:30,820 --> 00:17:33,220
 It's going to answer the questions of who and why.

445
00:17:33,220 --> 00:17:35,900
 It's going to help you understand your purpose.

446
00:17:35,900 --> 00:17:38,460
 And as we look at chapter one specifically,

447
00:17:38,460 --> 00:17:43,460
 what we know is that God has much to say about himself.

448
00:17:43,460 --> 00:17:46,100
 Now, we're not going to look at all of these,

449
00:17:46,100 --> 00:17:48,220
 but very briefly, like in just this one verse,

450
00:17:48,220 --> 00:17:49,380
 like we didn't get very far.

451
00:17:49,380 --> 00:17:53,020
 We didn't even get through the entire opening introduction

452
00:17:53,020 --> 00:17:53,860
 of this book.

453
00:17:53,860 --> 00:17:55,700
 And yet in the first verse, what we see about God

454
00:17:55,700 --> 00:17:59,540
 is God is telling us that he is infinite.

455
00:17:59,540 --> 00:18:01,220
 He is limitless.

456
00:18:01,220 --> 00:18:03,980
 Like at the beginning, he was already there.

457
00:18:03,980 --> 00:18:05,060
 He's outside of time.

458
00:18:05,060 --> 00:18:06,900
 And what's amazing about his infinitude

459
00:18:06,900 --> 00:18:10,520
 is it actually undergirds every other quality of him,

460
00:18:10,520 --> 00:18:11,420
 which is amazing.

461
00:18:11,420 --> 00:18:15,060
 His grace for that sin, which you feel like, gosh,

462
00:18:15,060 --> 00:18:18,460
 I'm so tired of apologizing and seeking forgiveness

463
00:18:18,460 --> 00:18:19,280
 for these things.

464
00:18:19,280 --> 00:18:21,620
 His grace is limitless.

465
00:18:21,620 --> 00:18:23,740
 It goes on and on and on and on and on.

466
00:18:23,740 --> 00:18:25,340
 His mercy, limitless.

467
00:18:25,340 --> 00:18:28,700
 His patience with you, it is limitless.

468
00:18:28,700 --> 00:18:32,500
 His understanding of what's going on in your life,

469
00:18:32,500 --> 00:18:33,340
 it is limitless.

470
00:18:33,340 --> 00:18:35,420
 God is limitless, but that's not the primary thing

471
00:18:35,420 --> 00:18:36,460
 we learn about him here.

472
00:18:36,460 --> 00:18:39,340
 We also see that he is self-revealed.

473
00:18:39,340 --> 00:18:40,260
 I love this.

474
00:18:40,260 --> 00:18:43,220
 It tells us in Romans 1:20, that through his creation,

475
00:18:43,220 --> 00:18:45,980
 God's invisible attributes, namely his eternal power

476
00:18:45,980 --> 00:18:48,540
 and his divine nature, are clearly perceived

477
00:18:48,540 --> 00:18:49,660
 ever since the creation of the world

478
00:18:49,660 --> 00:18:50,580
 and the things that have been made.

479
00:18:50,580 --> 00:18:52,280
 So we are without excuse.

480
00:18:52,280 --> 00:18:54,900
 What this is telling us is God is self-revealed.

481
00:18:54,900 --> 00:18:56,700
 Like nobody stumbled upon God,

482
00:18:56,700 --> 00:18:58,580
 like the unknown wonder of the world.

483
00:18:58,580 --> 00:18:59,580
 And they began to publish it

484
00:18:59,580 --> 00:19:01,100
 so they could get a bunch of popularity.

485
00:19:01,100 --> 00:19:01,940
 That's not what happened.

486
00:19:01,940 --> 00:19:05,380
 Nobody arrived at this revelation by themself.

487
00:19:05,380 --> 00:19:07,900
 God was already revealing himself all along.

488
00:19:07,900 --> 00:19:09,460
 But that's not the key thing that Genesis 1

489
00:19:09,460 --> 00:19:10,580
 is wanting to tell us about him.

490
00:19:10,580 --> 00:19:12,460
 We also learn that he's sovereign.

491
00:19:12,460 --> 00:19:15,340
 When it says that he made the heavens and the earth,

492
00:19:15,340 --> 00:19:18,780
 the thought there is heavens and earth encapsulate

493
00:19:18,780 --> 00:19:21,860
 everything known in creation,

494
00:19:21,860 --> 00:19:24,360
 as well as everything unknown in creation.

495
00:19:25,380 --> 00:19:30,380
 God is the uncaused cause of all of it.

496
00:19:30,380 --> 00:19:33,940
 He is the primary character of the cosmos.

497
00:19:33,940 --> 00:19:36,620
 And yet, not only did he create it,

498
00:19:36,620 --> 00:19:38,700
 he rules and reigns over it.

499
00:19:38,700 --> 00:19:39,940
 He's sovereign.

500
00:19:39,940 --> 00:19:42,060
 But that's also not the primary thing

501
00:19:42,060 --> 00:19:44,180
 that we need to learn about who God is.

502
00:19:44,180 --> 00:19:46,180
 In an effort to know who God is,

503
00:19:46,180 --> 00:19:47,980
 what Genesis wants to let you know

504
00:19:47,980 --> 00:19:52,700
 is that God is, according to this text,

505
00:19:52,700 --> 00:19:54,880
 he should be known as creator.

506
00:19:55,480 --> 00:19:57,360
 God is creator.

507
00:19:57,360 --> 00:20:01,240
 That's the big title to understand about who God is.

508
00:20:01,240 --> 00:20:05,000
 Which it took us all of one verse to figure that out.

509
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:06,780
 So now you're probably wondering,

510
00:20:06,780 --> 00:20:08,360
 what is the rest of this chapter about?

511
00:20:08,360 --> 00:20:10,280
 There are 31 more verses here, Kylan.

512
00:20:10,280 --> 00:20:13,040
 I'm not real sure if this is all described to us

513
00:20:13,040 --> 00:20:14,680
 that he is creator in just one verse.

514
00:20:14,680 --> 00:20:17,000
 What is the rest of this chapter actually going to explain?

515
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:18,440
 Well, it's important for you to understand.

516
00:20:18,440 --> 00:20:20,400
 You need to understand that though the first verse

517
00:20:20,400 --> 00:20:21,640
 gives you God's creative character,

518
00:20:21,640 --> 00:20:24,680
 the rest of the verses give you God's creative nature.

519
00:20:24,680 --> 00:20:26,480
 His creative nature.

520
00:20:26,480 --> 00:20:28,520
 I remember growing up,

521
00:20:28,520 --> 00:20:31,880
 we would go to this local restaurant in my hometown.

522
00:20:31,880 --> 00:20:34,760
 And inside of it, there was a sign that said,

523
00:20:34,760 --> 00:20:36,400
 never trust a skinny cook.

524
00:20:36,400 --> 00:20:39,380
 Now I'm not saying that that's good advice,

525
00:20:39,380 --> 00:20:41,800
 but what I am saying is my young mind

526
00:20:41,800 --> 00:20:43,560
 could actually understand what it was describing.

527
00:20:43,560 --> 00:20:47,380
 It was telling me that actions speak louder than words.

528
00:20:47,380 --> 00:20:49,200
 And so what we need to understand is that ladies,

529
00:20:49,200 --> 00:20:50,760
 if you want to confirm if he's a gentleman,

530
00:20:50,760 --> 00:20:52,200
 you should see the way that he treats the waitstaff

531
00:20:52,200 --> 00:20:54,080
 when you go on a date.

532
00:20:54,080 --> 00:20:56,680
 If you want to see if someone's a good leader,

533
00:20:56,680 --> 00:20:58,720
 you should think about the way that their employees

534
00:20:58,720 --> 00:21:00,640
 or followers speak about them.

535
00:21:00,640 --> 00:21:03,040
 And if you want to understand what kind of creator God is,

536
00:21:03,040 --> 00:21:04,680
 you need not only look at what he has created,

537
00:21:04,680 --> 00:21:06,600
 you need to look at the way in which he created.

538
00:21:06,600 --> 00:21:08,040
 Does that make sense?

539
00:21:08,040 --> 00:21:09,720
 That's what this is about.

540
00:21:09,720 --> 00:21:13,520
 It's going to tell you the way he created.

541
00:21:13,520 --> 00:21:16,840
 And as we see it, we learn more about him.

542
00:21:16,840 --> 00:21:19,960
 There are three things that we see very specifically.

543
00:21:19,960 --> 00:21:21,720
 Verse two, it tells us,

544
00:21:21,720 --> 00:21:24,800
 the earth was without form and void,

545
00:21:24,800 --> 00:21:27,320
 and darkness is over the face of the deep.

546
00:21:27,320 --> 00:21:30,920
 The earth was what the Hebrew describes as tohu and bohu.

547
00:21:30,920 --> 00:21:34,080
 It had no form and it had no fill.

548
00:21:34,080 --> 00:21:36,600
 Another way of thinking about that is it had no structure

549
00:21:36,600 --> 00:21:37,880
 and it had no substance.

550
00:21:37,880 --> 00:21:40,040
 So what's God doing in this story?

551
00:21:40,040 --> 00:21:45,040
 He is preparing a world, a place for people to live.

552
00:21:45,040 --> 00:21:48,520
 And yet there's no structure and there's no substance.

553
00:21:48,520 --> 00:21:50,920
 Meaning there, if we're going to use an analogy

554
00:21:50,920 --> 00:21:51,760
 of something like a house,

555
00:21:51,760 --> 00:21:54,200
 there are no walls and there's no furnishing.

556
00:21:54,200 --> 00:21:56,040
 So what then is there in this moment?

557
00:21:56,040 --> 00:21:59,280
 A foundation, that's it.

558
00:21:59,280 --> 00:22:02,520
 All that is here in this moment, according to verse two,

559
00:22:02,520 --> 00:22:06,120
 is a foundation, something upon which you can build.

560
00:22:06,120 --> 00:22:10,140
 It describes it as this chaotic disorder, primordial water.

561
00:22:10,140 --> 00:22:11,540
 But more on that next week.

562
00:22:11,540 --> 00:22:15,120
 Naturally, what we need to ask is if God is going to build

563
00:22:15,120 --> 00:22:20,120
 a home for all people, what then should he do next?

564
00:22:21,120 --> 00:22:25,400
 What anyone would do, he should put structure in place.

565
00:22:25,400 --> 00:22:27,120
 He should raise up some walls,

566
00:22:27,120 --> 00:22:31,360
 which is exactly what we see in days one, two, and three.

567
00:22:31,360 --> 00:22:33,460
 It says that he creates light and dark,

568
00:22:33,460 --> 00:22:36,440
 sky and waters, and land and sea.

569
00:22:36,440 --> 00:22:38,600
 But notice this, he doesn't just stop there

570
00:22:38,600 --> 00:22:42,200
 because the walls of a house don't make a home, do they?

571
00:22:42,200 --> 00:22:44,780
 It's what's inside that makes a home.

572
00:22:44,780 --> 00:22:49,360
 There needs to be substance within the structure

573
00:22:49,360 --> 00:22:50,460
 of God's creation.

574
00:22:50,460 --> 00:22:53,480
 That's what makes it feel complete,

575
00:22:53,480 --> 00:22:56,280
 which is exactly what God goes on to do next.

576
00:22:56,280 --> 00:22:57,560
 It's incredible.

577
00:22:57,560 --> 00:23:01,040
 God, in the first set of three days,

578
00:23:01,040 --> 00:23:03,480
 provides all of the structure.

579
00:23:03,480 --> 00:23:05,560
 And then in the second set of three days,

580
00:23:05,560 --> 00:23:07,240
 he provides all of the substance.

581
00:23:07,240 --> 00:23:10,440
 And the beauty of it is, it's not random.

582
00:23:10,440 --> 00:23:12,360
 It's reflective.

583
00:23:12,360 --> 00:23:13,200
 Here's what I mean.

584
00:23:13,200 --> 00:23:16,140
 I think we can put this on the screens to help describe it.

585
00:23:16,140 --> 00:23:20,640
 On day one, God created the structures of night and day.

586
00:23:20,640 --> 00:23:24,780
 And correspondingly on day four,

587
00:23:24,780 --> 00:23:27,100
 the first day of the second set of three,

588
00:23:27,100 --> 00:23:30,560
 he creates the substance for that night and day.

589
00:23:30,560 --> 00:23:34,100
 He creates the sun, the moon, and the stars.

590
00:23:34,100 --> 00:23:38,820
 On day two, he puts the structure of the sky and waters.

591
00:23:38,820 --> 00:23:42,840
 And on day five, the corresponding second day

592
00:23:42,840 --> 00:23:44,340
 in the second set of three,

593
00:23:44,340 --> 00:23:46,420
 he creates the substance of birds and fish

594
00:23:46,420 --> 00:23:48,000
 to fill those skies and waters.

595
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:49,340
 Do you see it?

596
00:23:49,340 --> 00:23:51,540
 And on day three, where he created the structure

597
00:23:51,540 --> 00:23:55,380
 of land from the water, day six, we see,

598
00:23:55,380 --> 00:23:58,620
 he creates the corresponding substance for that structure.

599
00:23:58,620 --> 00:24:02,420
 He creates the beasts of the field and humans.

600
00:24:02,420 --> 00:24:04,380
 Isn't that amazing?

601
00:24:04,380 --> 00:24:08,420
 Like, do you see what God's trying to tell us about himself?

602
00:24:08,420 --> 00:24:11,540
 Not that he's type A, even though he's clearly organized.

603
00:24:11,540 --> 00:24:14,100
 What he's trying to say is that he's intentional.

604
00:24:14,100 --> 00:24:18,180
 You see, God, he created the world intentionally,

605
00:24:18,180 --> 00:24:23,180
 not indifferently, which is a huge thing for us to consider

606
00:24:23,180 --> 00:24:26,180
 because he isn't haphazard or disinterested in his creation

607
00:24:26,180 --> 00:24:27,100
 like some people believe.

608
00:24:27,100 --> 00:24:29,020
 Like some people think that God, sure,

609
00:24:29,020 --> 00:24:31,140
 he created everything, but he spun it like a top

610
00:24:31,140 --> 00:24:34,180
 and he left it to wobble around on its own.

611
00:24:34,180 --> 00:24:35,020
 But that's not true.

612
00:24:35,020 --> 00:24:36,820
 He is deeply invested.

613
00:24:36,820 --> 00:24:41,340
 He is deeply intentional with the affairs of our world.

614
00:24:41,340 --> 00:24:42,860
 He put all of this structure

615
00:24:42,860 --> 00:24:44,460
 and he filled it with all of this substance.

616
00:24:44,460 --> 00:24:46,320
 I should have brought this as an illustration,

617
00:24:46,320 --> 00:24:48,740
 but it would be as if I gave you a vase structure

618
00:24:48,740 --> 00:24:50,860
 and I filled it with flowers, substance.

619
00:24:50,860 --> 00:24:52,020
 See what God did?

620
00:24:52,020 --> 00:24:54,560
 He is producing the constructs of creation

621
00:24:54,560 --> 00:24:57,220
 so that life can flourish.

622
00:24:57,220 --> 00:24:59,140
 And we do this too.

623
00:24:59,140 --> 00:25:01,580
 Like, I don't know what kind of look you're going for

624
00:25:01,580 --> 00:25:03,740
 in your house, and yet more than likely in your house,

625
00:25:03,740 --> 00:25:05,700
 you're trying to strike some sort of vibe,

626
00:25:05,700 --> 00:25:07,740
 whether it's mid-century modern or Scandinavian,

627
00:25:07,740 --> 00:25:08,840
 I don't know what your thing is,

628
00:25:08,840 --> 00:25:11,700
 but you are trying to structure and fill that space

629
00:25:11,700 --> 00:25:14,060
 in a way that produces what?

630
00:25:14,060 --> 00:25:15,580
 Flourishing.

631
00:25:15,580 --> 00:25:17,220
 Maybe it's a playlist that you listen to

632
00:25:17,220 --> 00:25:18,300
 whenever you go running,

633
00:25:18,300 --> 00:25:20,580
 but no other playlist that someone has made

634
00:25:20,580 --> 00:25:21,640
 is going to qualify.

635
00:25:21,640 --> 00:25:23,740
 No, you must curate it yourself.

636
00:25:23,740 --> 00:25:26,940
 You must structure what you want the atmosphere

637
00:25:26,940 --> 00:25:28,220
 of that playlist to play,

638
00:25:28,220 --> 00:25:30,300
 and then you must fill it with your own songs

639
00:25:30,300 --> 00:25:31,780
 because that produces flourishing.

640
00:25:31,780 --> 00:25:34,180
 Others of you, you've got a power outfit.

641
00:25:34,180 --> 00:25:35,420
 You've worked really hard on it.

642
00:25:35,420 --> 00:25:37,260
 You have structured together that,

643
00:25:37,260 --> 00:25:39,720
 which is going to ultimately help you express

644
00:25:39,720 --> 00:25:41,240
 the greatest levels of confidence

645
00:25:41,240 --> 00:25:42,960
 you can have whenever you step into the world.

646
00:25:42,960 --> 00:25:45,380
 We do this all the time.

647
00:25:45,380 --> 00:25:47,980
 We organize our lives in a way that produces flourishing.

648
00:25:47,980 --> 00:25:49,700
 I remember one of my college roommates,

649
00:25:49,700 --> 00:25:52,520
 he was dating this girl around Christmas time,

650
00:25:52,520 --> 00:25:53,820
 and he was really into her.

651
00:25:53,820 --> 00:25:55,540
 He liked her a whole lot,

652
00:25:55,540 --> 00:25:57,060
 and so in an effort to make sure

653
00:25:57,060 --> 00:25:59,340
 that things would continue to go really well,

654
00:25:59,340 --> 00:26:02,140
 he did the inexplicable.

655
00:26:02,140 --> 00:26:05,620
 He rented a Christmas tree farm,

656
00:26:05,620 --> 00:26:06,820
 which I didn't know you could do that.

657
00:26:06,820 --> 00:26:09,020
 He rented a Christmas tree farm, but not just that.

658
00:26:09,020 --> 00:26:12,200
 He also, he went and he purchased snowballs

659
00:26:12,200 --> 00:26:13,560
 from a local snow cone shop,

660
00:26:13,560 --> 00:26:14,880
 and then he ensured that the two of them

661
00:26:14,880 --> 00:26:16,480
 could have a private snowball fight,

662
00:26:16,480 --> 00:26:18,840
 just the two of them in this Christmas tree farm

663
00:26:18,840 --> 00:26:20,480
 with no one else around.

664
00:26:20,480 --> 00:26:21,960
 Why would he go to all this trouble?

665
00:26:21,960 --> 00:26:24,800
 Because that is the recipe for success, gentlemen.

666
00:26:24,800 --> 00:26:27,160
 That's what it looks like to woo a woman

667
00:26:27,160 --> 00:26:29,860
 and bring her into a relationship,

668
00:26:29,860 --> 00:26:32,060
 except for the fact that their relationship ultimately ended.

669
00:26:32,060 --> 00:26:34,680
 What you need to know is that he wanted

670
00:26:34,680 --> 00:26:36,320
 to provide the structure and the substance

671
00:26:36,320 --> 00:26:38,540
 that would ultimately lead them to a thriving

672
00:26:38,540 --> 00:26:40,880
 and not just surviving type of relationship.

673
00:26:40,880 --> 00:26:42,480
 God does the same thing.

674
00:26:42,480 --> 00:26:44,680
 Now, as I say that, I know that can feel

675
00:26:44,680 --> 00:26:46,960
 really hard to believe for some of you,

676
00:26:46,960 --> 00:26:47,960
 because the truth of the matter is,

677
00:26:47,960 --> 00:26:49,480
 you may hear that God is intentional,

678
00:26:49,480 --> 00:26:51,660
 but what you experience in your own life,

679
00:26:51,660 --> 00:26:53,860
 what is closest to your own reality,

680
00:26:53,860 --> 00:26:56,440
 is that he's very indifferent.

681
00:26:56,440 --> 00:27:00,560
 You hear and you feel like, man, he doesn't see me.

682
00:27:00,560 --> 00:27:01,920
 He doesn't care about me.

683
00:27:01,920 --> 00:27:04,640
 He doesn't listen to me.

684
00:27:04,640 --> 00:27:06,240
 I've prayed the right prayers.

685
00:27:06,240 --> 00:27:08,440
 I've been steadfast in the face of trial.

686
00:27:08,440 --> 00:27:10,140
 I've pursued faithfulness.

687
00:27:10,140 --> 00:27:11,020
 And what have I gotten for it?

688
00:27:11,020 --> 00:27:12,720
 I've got nothing, Kylan.

689
00:27:12,720 --> 00:27:14,220
 Nothing good has come to me.

690
00:27:14,220 --> 00:27:16,060
 God has not been intentional.

691
00:27:16,060 --> 00:27:18,360
 He has only been indifferent.

692
00:27:18,360 --> 00:27:21,280
 If that's you, would you just hear me?

693
00:27:21,280 --> 00:27:24,800
 It is not that God is indifferent towards you.

694
00:27:24,800 --> 00:27:30,980
 In fact, it is that God is being extra intentional with you.

695
00:27:30,980 --> 00:27:34,620
 Because for those times in life

696
00:27:34,620 --> 00:27:36,380
 where things feel so complicated

697
00:27:36,380 --> 00:27:38,820
 and they make no sense at all,

698
00:27:38,820 --> 00:27:41,820
 God is often, not always, but often,

699
00:27:41,820 --> 00:27:46,100
 leading us into places we would not go

700
00:27:46,100 --> 00:27:49,320
 so that we can grow.

701
00:27:49,320 --> 00:27:54,020
 He does this all the time,

702
00:27:54,020 --> 00:27:57,120
 and he does it because he is a good father.

703
00:27:57,120 --> 00:28:00,100
 I got to relate to this reality

704
00:28:00,100 --> 00:28:01,540
 really clearly this last week,

705
00:28:01,540 --> 00:28:03,320
 because we took our little baby boy

706
00:28:03,320 --> 00:28:06,960
 and we shipped him off to daycare for the very first time.

707
00:28:06,960 --> 00:28:09,580
 And I'll just level with you.

708
00:28:09,580 --> 00:28:11,660
 I wasn't excited about it at all.

709
00:28:11,660 --> 00:28:14,940
 Like, I would much rather keep him in our house

710
00:28:14,940 --> 00:28:16,780
 and ensure that he never feels abandoned,

711
00:28:16,780 --> 00:28:18,300
 he never feels unloved.

712
00:28:18,300 --> 00:28:20,800
 And yet at the same time, I know, dude, you need to grow up.

713
00:28:20,800 --> 00:28:21,640
 Like, you need to realize

714
00:28:21,640 --> 00:28:22,980
 that the world doesn't revolve around you.

715
00:28:22,980 --> 00:28:25,220
 You got to learn how to socialize and share some toys

716
00:28:25,220 --> 00:28:26,860
 and make sure that you actually

717
00:28:26,860 --> 00:28:28,300
 are a good contributor to society.

718
00:28:28,300 --> 00:28:29,980
 Like, I've got to help you become

719
00:28:29,980 --> 00:28:31,220
 what you're meant to become.

720
00:28:31,220 --> 00:28:32,420
 And yet if you stay here,

721
00:28:32,420 --> 00:28:33,680
 you're not going to be able to do that.

722
00:28:33,680 --> 00:28:34,520
 And so what did we do?

723
00:28:34,520 --> 00:28:37,480
 We led him to his inevitable doomsday,

724
00:28:37,480 --> 00:28:39,520
 and we shipped him off, we put him in daycare.

725
00:28:39,520 --> 00:28:41,640
 And yet here was the thing, the night before we did it,

726
00:28:41,640 --> 00:28:43,160
 Brooke and I, we were laying in bed,

727
00:28:43,160 --> 00:28:45,360
 and both of us still, we felt this anxiety.

728
00:28:45,360 --> 00:28:48,360
 We're like, man, we know it's right, but gosh, it's so hard.

729
00:28:48,360 --> 00:28:51,240
 Like, what if he feels abandoned by us?

730
00:28:51,240 --> 00:28:52,760
 He's never been outside of our home.

731
00:28:52,760 --> 00:28:54,540
 He's never been left by himself.

732
00:28:54,540 --> 00:28:55,940
 What if he feels abandoned?

733
00:28:55,940 --> 00:29:00,040
 Well, he doesn't know this,

734
00:29:01,040 --> 00:29:03,460
 but we've always got an eye on him

735
00:29:03,460 --> 00:29:06,260
 because we literally have a live feed into his classroom.

736
00:29:06,260 --> 00:29:09,780
 What if he feels unloved?

737
00:29:09,780 --> 00:29:11,100
 Like, what if he gets dropped in a place

738
00:29:11,100 --> 00:29:13,440
 he knows nothing about and he totally feels unloved?

739
00:29:13,440 --> 00:29:16,140
 Well, he may feel that way, but the reality is

740
00:29:16,140 --> 00:29:19,880
 we looked high and low for the best daycare possible,

741
00:29:19,880 --> 00:29:22,700
 and we tested them thoroughly

742
00:29:22,700 --> 00:29:24,940
 to make sure they would take care of our boy.

743
00:29:24,940 --> 00:29:27,820
 And in those moments when he feels like mom and dad

744
00:29:27,820 --> 00:29:29,900
 are never going to show up,

745
00:29:29,900 --> 00:29:32,560
 we know five o'clock's coming,

746
00:29:32,560 --> 00:29:35,640
 and we're gonna be there waiting for you,

747
00:29:35,640 --> 00:29:37,920
 ready to pick you up and take you home.

748
00:29:37,920 --> 00:29:40,920
 I think God feels very similar to you

749
00:29:40,920 --> 00:29:43,120
 in your moment of pain and difficulty.

750
00:29:43,120 --> 00:29:47,480
 I think he dreads sending you into the wilderness,

751
00:29:47,480 --> 00:29:50,560
 but he wants us to know when you feel abandoned,

752
00:29:50,560 --> 00:29:51,640
 I've got an eye on you.

753
00:29:51,640 --> 00:29:54,820
 When you feel unloved, I've already gone before you,

754
00:29:54,820 --> 00:29:57,620
 and when you're worried I'll never show up, don't worry.

755
00:29:58,480 --> 00:30:00,780
 I'm waiting for the moment to come.

756
00:30:00,780 --> 00:30:02,300
 That's who he is.

757
00:30:02,300 --> 00:30:05,900
 Like, God, he is intentional.

758
00:30:05,900 --> 00:30:07,900
 He is not indifferent.

759
00:30:07,900 --> 00:30:11,180
 And we see this expressed not just as he declares it to us,

760
00:30:11,180 --> 00:30:15,160
 but as he exemplifies it to us through the person of Jesus.

761
00:30:15,160 --> 00:30:17,460
 Jesus, we know in Hebrews 12, too,

762
00:30:17,460 --> 00:30:20,180
 for the joy that was set before him, he endured the cross.

763
00:30:20,180 --> 00:30:21,340
 Do you see that?

764
00:30:21,340 --> 00:30:23,460
 He entered into immense difficulty,

765
00:30:23,460 --> 00:30:26,180
 the likes of which you will never understand,

766
00:30:26,180 --> 00:30:27,460
 and he despised that shame,

767
00:30:27,460 --> 00:30:28,740
 and now he is sitting at the right hand

768
00:30:28,740 --> 00:30:29,660
 of the throne of God.

769
00:30:29,660 --> 00:30:32,780
 You see, Jesus himself, he understood sometimes

770
00:30:32,780 --> 00:30:35,980
 it's gotta get harder before it gets better.

771
00:30:35,980 --> 00:30:39,060
 Sometimes the path to life

772
00:30:39,060 --> 00:30:42,420
 goes through the valley of death.

773
00:30:42,420 --> 00:30:46,080
 God is intentional with you, I promise.

774
00:30:46,080 --> 00:30:48,140
 He is declaring it from Genesis 1,

775
00:30:48,140 --> 00:30:50,940
 and he is declaring it to you today.

776
00:30:50,940 --> 00:30:51,780
 And this would have been something

777
00:30:51,780 --> 00:30:52,600
 that the ancient Israelites

778
00:30:52,600 --> 00:30:54,040
 would have been processing themselves.

779
00:30:54,400 --> 00:30:58,360
 That idea of, man, is God actually going to lead me

780
00:30:58,360 --> 00:31:01,560
 through difficulty for my own development?

781
00:31:01,560 --> 00:31:05,200
 The reality is they would have been chewing on this, too.

782
00:31:05,200 --> 00:31:06,840
 Contextually, you need to know,

783
00:31:06,840 --> 00:31:09,240
 the book of Genesis was written by Moses,

784
00:31:09,240 --> 00:31:12,280
 and it was given to him by God

785
00:31:12,280 --> 00:31:15,560
 whenever he had led the Israelites out of Egyptian slavery

786
00:31:15,560 --> 00:31:17,480
 and into the wilderness, there at Mount Sinai.

787
00:31:17,480 --> 00:31:19,360
 And so what he's doing is Moses

788
00:31:19,360 --> 00:31:22,080
 is teaching these same truths to a group of people

789
00:31:22,080 --> 00:31:24,640
 that have just been liberated out of captivity.

790
00:31:24,640 --> 00:31:26,160
 They are a group of refugees.

791
00:31:26,160 --> 00:31:29,560
 They are 2 million in number, men, women, and children.

792
00:31:29,560 --> 00:31:31,920
 And what he is declaring to them is that,

793
00:31:31,920 --> 00:31:34,640
 yes, you may have been in Egypt, it may have been a part,

794
00:31:34,640 --> 00:31:36,500
 but God has come to get you out.

795
00:31:36,500 --> 00:31:38,260
 And yet, here's the thing that we see

796
00:31:38,260 --> 00:31:39,640
 as we continue to read into the story.

797
00:31:39,640 --> 00:31:41,560
 We know that God looks at them and he says,

798
00:31:41,560 --> 00:31:44,480
 man, yeah, they are set free of their circumstance,

799
00:31:44,480 --> 00:31:47,640
 and yet their circumstance has really done a number on them.

800
00:31:47,640 --> 00:31:50,000
 Like, yeah, I got them out of Egypt,

801
00:31:50,000 --> 00:31:52,120
 but now I gotta get Egypt out of them.

802
00:31:52,120 --> 00:31:53,880
 That's what we see as he keeps going.

803
00:31:53,880 --> 00:31:56,360
 He realizes they have been conditioned

804
00:31:56,360 --> 00:32:00,960
 into believing some lies that they need to unlearn.

805
00:32:00,960 --> 00:32:02,960
 And so to help them unlearn them,

806
00:32:02,960 --> 00:32:06,300
 what we see is he continues to speak.

807
00:32:06,300 --> 00:32:10,220
 And he speaks to them in a principle that reminds them,

808
00:32:10,220 --> 00:32:14,560
 hey, in Egypt, you were valued for what you do.

809
00:32:14,560 --> 00:32:17,360
 Your value, it correlated

810
00:32:17,360 --> 00:32:19,780
 with how many bricks he can make for Pharaoh.

811
00:32:19,780 --> 00:32:22,220
 But now, you're not valued for what you do,

812
00:32:22,220 --> 00:32:24,400
 you're valued for who you are.

813
00:32:24,400 --> 00:32:26,680
 Because God wants them to know and he wants you to know.

814
00:32:26,680 --> 00:32:29,980
 God created human beings, not human doings.

815
00:32:29,980 --> 00:32:33,960
 God created human beings, not human doings.

816
00:32:33,960 --> 00:32:35,700
 That's why we read in verse five,

817
00:32:35,700 --> 00:32:38,480
 and there was evening and morning the first day.

818
00:32:38,480 --> 00:32:39,520
 And then we read in verse eight,

819
00:32:39,520 --> 00:32:41,840
 and there was evening and morning the second day.

820
00:32:41,840 --> 00:32:43,840
 And in verse 13, there was evening and morning

821
00:32:43,840 --> 00:32:44,680
 the third day.

822
00:32:44,680 --> 00:32:46,420
 Isn't that crazy?

823
00:32:46,420 --> 00:32:47,260
 Mind-blowing!

824
00:32:47,760 --> 00:32:49,920
 Maybe it doesn't strike us as such,

825
00:32:49,920 --> 00:32:53,360
 because we don't realize just how subtly significant

826
00:32:53,360 --> 00:32:55,080
 what we're reading here actually is.

827
00:32:55,080 --> 00:32:58,960
 And yet, this is a massive point of importance.

828
00:32:58,960 --> 00:33:02,080
 Because what God is saying is he is saying,

829
00:33:02,080 --> 00:33:06,600
 you're valued for who you are, not what you do.

830
00:33:06,600 --> 00:33:08,400
 Let me describe it to you like this.

831
00:33:08,400 --> 00:33:09,520
 What do you do in your mornings?

832
00:33:09,520 --> 00:33:11,720
 What do your mornings represent in your life?

833
00:33:11,720 --> 00:33:15,240
 More than likely, they represent something

834
00:33:15,240 --> 00:33:16,340
 that you're not used to.

835
00:33:16,340 --> 00:33:18,980
 More than likely, they represent things like stress.

836
00:33:18,980 --> 00:33:20,820
 Stress over the fact that it's busy season

837
00:33:20,820 --> 00:33:23,140
 and your boss has high expectations.

838
00:33:23,140 --> 00:33:25,660
 Anxiety, because you know you gotta have

839
00:33:25,660 --> 00:33:26,500
 that conversation today,

840
00:33:26,500 --> 00:33:29,060
 and you were dreading having that conversation.

841
00:33:29,060 --> 00:33:31,840
 Dread, because you woke up to 15 emails

842
00:33:31,840 --> 00:33:32,900
 even when people should have been sleeping.

843
00:33:32,900 --> 00:33:34,100
 Somehow, they're still working,

844
00:33:34,100 --> 00:33:36,680
 and now you've gotta answer all of this stuff.

845
00:33:36,680 --> 00:33:39,740
 The mornings often represent productivity,

846
00:33:39,740 --> 00:33:42,420
 performance, demand.

847
00:33:44,240 --> 00:33:46,620
 Now, what do the evenings represent?

848
00:33:46,620 --> 00:33:50,460
 The evenings represent kicking your feet up,

849
00:33:50,460 --> 00:33:53,620
 curling up on the couch, winding down

850
00:33:53,620 --> 00:33:56,420
 at the end of a long day with some good food,

851
00:33:56,420 --> 00:34:00,220
 maybe a glass of wine, making sure that

852
00:34:00,220 --> 00:34:01,960
 before you hit the hay, you open a book,

853
00:34:01,960 --> 00:34:04,460
 or you watch that show that you're interested in.

854
00:34:04,460 --> 00:34:09,460
 The evening represents rest, peace, supply.

855
00:34:09,460 --> 00:34:12,760
 That's why you look forward to it so much.

856
00:34:12,760 --> 00:34:13,860
 That's why you're watching the clock,

857
00:34:13,860 --> 00:34:15,360
 and you can't wait to get out at five.

858
00:34:15,360 --> 00:34:18,620
 You know, man, that's where rest is found.

859
00:34:18,620 --> 00:34:20,860
 We live in a world that orders our days

860
00:34:20,860 --> 00:34:23,020
 morning to evening, but God is looking at them,

861
00:34:23,020 --> 00:34:24,260
 and he's saying, "No, no, no, no, no.

862
00:34:24,260 --> 00:34:26,040
 "Our day is ordered opposite.

863
00:34:26,040 --> 00:34:27,940
 "Our day is ordered evening to morning,

864
00:34:27,940 --> 00:34:31,260
 "because I don't want you working for rest.

865
00:34:31,260 --> 00:34:34,100
 "I want you working from rest.

866
00:34:34,100 --> 00:34:38,340
 "I don't want you waking up and feeling all the rush

867
00:34:38,340 --> 00:34:41,480
 "and demand of having to go and do.

868
00:34:41,480 --> 00:34:45,660
 "I want you waking up and feeling the blessing

869
00:34:45,660 --> 00:34:50,140
 "that you are perfectly accepted by way of who you are,

870
00:34:50,140 --> 00:34:51,840
 "apart from anything you do."

871
00:34:51,840 --> 00:34:56,400
 Genesis 1:27 tells us something

872
00:34:56,400 --> 00:34:58,480
 really important about our value.

873
00:34:58,480 --> 00:35:00,300
 It says, "So God created man in his own image.

874
00:35:00,300 --> 00:35:01,400
 "In the image of God, he created him,

875
00:35:01,400 --> 00:35:03,260
 "male and female, he created them."

876
00:35:03,260 --> 00:35:05,500
 This is an idea in theological circles

877
00:35:05,500 --> 00:35:06,360
 known as the Imago Dei.

878
00:35:06,360 --> 00:35:07,320
 We're gonna spend a lot more time

879
00:35:07,320 --> 00:35:09,820
 talking about it next week, so if I don't

880
00:35:09,820 --> 00:35:11,700
 cut every angle on this for you,

881
00:35:11,700 --> 00:35:13,100
 then just come back next week,

882
00:35:13,100 --> 00:35:15,580
 'cause we're gonna talk extensively about this.

883
00:35:15,580 --> 00:35:18,140
 But one thing you have to understand about the Imago Dei

884
00:35:18,140 --> 00:35:21,980
 is it's describing to you where your worth comes from.

885
00:35:21,980 --> 00:35:23,140
 You see, it's saying that your self-worth

886
00:35:23,140 --> 00:35:26,100
 is not rooted in what you do, it's rooted in who you are.

887
00:35:26,100 --> 00:35:27,300
 So who does God say you are?

888
00:35:27,300 --> 00:35:31,140
 God is saying that you are made in his image.

889
00:35:31,140 --> 00:35:34,640
 That word image in the Hebrew is the word tselem.

890
00:35:34,640 --> 00:35:37,940
 It's T-S-E-L-E-M.

891
00:35:39,020 --> 00:35:40,100
 Tselem.

892
00:35:40,100 --> 00:35:45,100
 And the thought there is it represents an image or an idol.

893
00:35:45,100 --> 00:35:47,580
 Literally, God has made you an idol.

894
00:35:47,580 --> 00:35:50,040
 That's why he takes so much issue with there being idols

895
00:35:50,040 --> 00:35:50,940
 of other gods in the world,

896
00:35:50,940 --> 00:35:53,020
 because he has already filled the world with so many idols.

897
00:35:53,020 --> 00:35:54,980
 He has filled it with me and you.

898
00:35:54,980 --> 00:35:59,980
 You are a representative of his likeness everywhere you go.

899
00:35:59,980 --> 00:36:05,060
 You are a living, breathing, walking, talking

900
00:36:05,060 --> 00:36:07,860
 representation of who he is.

901
00:36:07,860 --> 00:36:10,540
 And there is no higher calling than that.

902
00:36:10,540 --> 00:36:13,460
 You are distinctly different than the rest of creation.

903
00:36:13,460 --> 00:36:16,580
 You are set apart because this is God's purpose

904
00:36:16,580 --> 00:36:17,420
 for your life.

905
00:36:17,420 --> 00:36:19,940
 It is not only to know him, it's to make him known.

906
00:36:19,940 --> 00:36:24,660
 Which means your sense of significance,

907
00:36:24,660 --> 00:36:26,560
 whatever sense of significance you find

908
00:36:26,560 --> 00:36:30,820
 in whatever it is you accomplish, you don't need it.

909
00:36:30,820 --> 00:36:34,460
 Because God has already declared you as significant.

910
00:36:34,460 --> 00:36:36,620
 When you don't feel like you matter

911
00:36:36,620 --> 00:36:39,000
 because you don't have enough zeros on your paycheck

912
00:36:39,000 --> 00:36:42,420
 or you don't have enough letters behind your name,

913
00:36:42,420 --> 00:36:44,460
 you don't need to matter anymore.

914
00:36:44,460 --> 00:36:45,580
 Because the truth of the matter is,

915
00:36:45,580 --> 00:36:48,060
 God has already declared that you matter.

916
00:36:48,060 --> 00:36:50,960
 Whenever you feel like you're not as important

917
00:36:50,960 --> 00:36:54,480
 as you want to be, you need know.

918
00:36:54,480 --> 00:36:56,660
 It doesn't take thousands or tens of thousands

919
00:36:56,660 --> 00:36:58,900
 or hundreds of thousands of followers to declare to you

920
00:36:58,900 --> 00:37:00,000
 that you're an important person

921
00:37:00,000 --> 00:37:02,900
 because God has already declared you are important.

922
00:37:02,900 --> 00:37:04,640
 Does that make sense to you?

923
00:37:04,640 --> 00:37:06,720
 This is so vital.

924
00:37:06,720 --> 00:37:09,880
 Now, as I say this, here's the thing that I know.

925
00:37:09,880 --> 00:37:12,140
 I know that so many Christians in the room,

926
00:37:12,140 --> 00:37:14,860
 so if you're not a believer, then just give me a minute

927
00:37:14,860 --> 00:37:16,080
 'cause I gotta have a family talk

928
00:37:16,080 --> 00:37:17,400
 with some of my brothers and sisters.

929
00:37:17,400 --> 00:37:19,320
 So many Christians in the room, they hear,

930
00:37:19,320 --> 00:37:20,840
 yeah, I'm made in the image of God,

931
00:37:20,840 --> 00:37:22,580
 and their brain turns off.

932
00:37:22,580 --> 00:37:25,280
 They're like, yeah, I know that, I got that, Colin,

933
00:37:25,280 --> 00:37:27,080
 thank you, I know that I'm valued for who I am,

934
00:37:27,080 --> 00:37:29,040
 I'm not valued for what I do, thanks.

935
00:37:29,040 --> 00:37:30,720
 But here's the reality, if you know it,

936
00:37:30,720 --> 00:37:33,240
 then why don't you live like it?

937
00:37:34,320 --> 00:37:37,560
 Why is it that you have so much insecurity?

938
00:37:37,560 --> 00:37:40,200
 Why is it that you live with so much false humility?

939
00:37:40,200 --> 00:37:42,640
 Why is it that you have this deep-rooted fear

940
00:37:42,640 --> 00:37:43,760
 of the future that you're trying

941
00:37:43,760 --> 00:37:46,160
 to control specific outcomes,

942
00:37:46,160 --> 00:37:48,980
 that you are so performative in Christian circles?

943
00:37:48,980 --> 00:37:50,920
 Why are you doing it?

944
00:37:50,920 --> 00:37:54,000
 That is a declaration that you do not understand

945
00:37:54,000 --> 00:37:55,360
 where your value comes from

946
00:37:55,360 --> 00:37:57,520
 because if you knew God gives my value,

947
00:37:57,520 --> 00:38:00,500
 you wouldn't be looking to the world to give you any more.

948
00:38:00,500 --> 00:38:05,240
 You would understand where your value is found,

949
00:38:05,240 --> 00:38:07,300
 which, follow me, and this is important,

950
00:38:07,300 --> 00:38:10,700
 if you're struggling with this,

951
00:38:10,700 --> 00:38:12,160
 it means you find greater worth

952
00:38:12,160 --> 00:38:13,320
 in what you can make of yourself

953
00:38:13,320 --> 00:38:15,080
 than what God can make of yourself.

954
00:38:15,080 --> 00:38:21,680
 You already have value, Christian.

955
00:38:21,680 --> 00:38:23,840
 Please live like it.

956
00:38:23,840 --> 00:38:26,700
 You are overestimating your ability

957
00:38:26,700 --> 00:38:29,720
 to think you can add anything to your worth.

958
00:38:30,720 --> 00:38:33,520
 Because not only did God give you worth at creation,

959
00:38:33,520 --> 00:38:37,740
 he redignified your worth at salvation.

960
00:38:37,740 --> 00:38:40,400
 He showed you, I made you right,

961
00:38:40,400 --> 00:38:43,080
 you screwed it up, and I came to make you right again.

962
00:38:43,080 --> 00:38:48,680
 You should be able to find rest in that truth.

963
00:38:48,680 --> 00:38:50,080
 That should lead you to a place

964
00:38:50,080 --> 00:38:52,840
 where you're able to take a load off.

965
00:38:52,840 --> 00:38:54,700
 And the reason I know that is because in that truth,

966
00:38:54,700 --> 00:38:55,880
 God rests himself.

967
00:38:55,880 --> 00:38:58,960
 That's what we see as we come to the end of this passage.

968
00:38:58,960 --> 00:39:01,200
 We see in Genesis 2, one through three,

969
00:39:01,200 --> 00:39:02,640
 I'm gonna read it again 'cause it's just important.

970
00:39:02,640 --> 00:39:03,640
 It says, "Thus the heavens and the earth,

971
00:39:03,640 --> 00:39:05,440
 "they were finished, and all the host of them,

972
00:39:05,440 --> 00:39:07,080
 "and on the seventh day, God finished his work

973
00:39:07,080 --> 00:39:09,200
 "that he had done, and he rested on the seventh day

974
00:39:09,200 --> 00:39:12,200
 "from all his work that he had done."

975
00:39:12,200 --> 00:39:14,200
 So God blessed the seventh day, and he made it holy

976
00:39:14,200 --> 00:39:15,840
 because on it, God rested from all his work

977
00:39:15,840 --> 00:39:17,760
 that he had done in creation.

978
00:39:17,760 --> 00:39:21,840
 I would have loved to have taught this

979
00:39:21,840 --> 00:39:24,160
 in a lecture kind of format, in a smaller room,

980
00:39:24,160 --> 00:39:25,200
 where we could put up things,

981
00:39:25,200 --> 00:39:26,280
 and I could draw them out for you,

982
00:39:26,280 --> 00:39:30,720
 because Genesis 1 is so poetically beautiful.

983
00:39:30,720 --> 00:39:33,500
 There is so much happening in the literature

984
00:39:33,500 --> 00:39:36,520
 of how Moses wrote this, inspired by the Spirit,

985
00:39:36,520 --> 00:39:38,800
 which unfortunately, we just don't have time to get into.

986
00:39:38,800 --> 00:39:40,280
 But one thing that you need to know

987
00:39:40,280 --> 00:39:43,800
 is there is this striking element

988
00:39:43,800 --> 00:39:45,460
 all throughout this chapter,

989
00:39:45,460 --> 00:39:49,920
 where we move in this rhythm of working to resting,

990
00:39:49,920 --> 00:39:51,000
 working to resting.

991
00:39:51,000 --> 00:39:51,840
 You see it.

992
00:39:51,840 --> 00:39:56,320
 It says that God spoke, it was good,

993
00:39:56,320 --> 00:39:58,280
 morning and evening, the day ended.

994
00:39:58,280 --> 00:40:00,880
 And that happens again and again and again and again,

995
00:40:00,880 --> 00:40:03,280
 until day seven.

996
00:40:03,280 --> 00:40:08,160
 Day seven is the day that never ends.

997
00:40:08,160 --> 00:40:14,520
 Day seven is not marked by any conclusive commentary.

998
00:40:14,520 --> 00:40:21,180
 It seems like this never-ending day of rest,

999
00:40:21,580 --> 00:40:22,600
 which I know some of you hear that,

1000
00:40:22,600 --> 00:40:24,780
 and you're like, oh man,

1001
00:40:24,780 --> 00:40:26,260
 I've been on the fence about Christianity,

1002
00:40:26,260 --> 00:40:28,360
 but if that's what I'm signing up for, put me in, coach.

1003
00:40:28,360 --> 00:40:29,980
 You know, like that's where so many of you are at,

1004
00:40:29,980 --> 00:40:33,240
 because you would love to jump into something

1005
00:40:33,240 --> 00:40:36,400
 where it affords you a little self-care treatment,

1006
00:40:36,400 --> 00:40:38,660
 a day at the spa, you know, a little retail therapy,

1007
00:40:38,660 --> 00:40:40,000
 maybe a golf trip with the boys.

1008
00:40:40,000 --> 00:40:41,800
 That's not what this is talking about.

1009
00:40:41,800 --> 00:40:45,240
 You see, we often mistake godly rest for worldly rest.

1010
00:40:45,240 --> 00:40:46,640
 But here's the difference in the two,

1011
00:40:46,640 --> 00:40:47,800
 and I want you to catch this.

1012
00:40:47,800 --> 00:40:50,200
 Worldly rest, it just wants to escape

1013
00:40:50,200 --> 00:40:52,440
 the sadness of reality.

1014
00:40:52,440 --> 00:40:55,840
 But godly rest, the kind of rest that God himself does,

1015
00:40:55,840 --> 00:41:00,480
 it wants to enjoy the goodness of reality.

1016
00:41:00,480 --> 00:41:03,200
 Worldly rest wants to escape the sadness of it all,

1017
00:41:03,200 --> 00:41:06,900
 but godly rest wants to enjoy the goodness of it all instead.

1018
00:41:06,900 --> 00:41:08,560
 That's why seven times he declares,

1019
00:41:08,560 --> 00:41:11,080
 this is good, this is good, this is good.

1020
00:41:11,080 --> 00:41:12,580
 Not because he did the job,

1021
00:41:12,580 --> 00:41:13,880
 like the Holy Spirit doesn't roll up and be like,

1022
00:41:13,880 --> 00:41:15,140
 man, like that lion, nice job,

1023
00:41:15,140 --> 00:41:16,060
 love what you did with the hair.

1024
00:41:16,060 --> 00:41:18,160
 Like that's not the way that this is working out.

1025
00:41:18,160 --> 00:41:19,240
 He looks at it and he says,

1026
00:41:19,240 --> 00:41:20,880
 it's not good because it's complete.

1027
00:41:20,880 --> 00:41:22,200
 It's good

1028
00:41:22,200 --> 00:41:27,180
 because it's from me.

1029
00:41:27,180 --> 00:41:30,800
 We have this idea when we read about the Garden of Eden

1030
00:41:30,800 --> 00:41:31,960
 that it's perfect,

1031
00:41:31,960 --> 00:41:34,920
 but that's not an ancient Near Eastern idea.

1032
00:41:34,920 --> 00:41:36,440
 They would not have assumed it was perfect

1033
00:41:36,440 --> 00:41:39,020
 'cause that would mean you could understand the end of it.

1034
00:41:39,020 --> 00:41:41,720
 But you cannot understand the end of God's goodness.

1035
00:41:41,720 --> 00:41:44,240
 It goes on and on and on and on,

1036
00:41:44,240 --> 00:41:47,100
 and his goodness is one which there is a total absence

1037
00:41:47,100 --> 00:41:50,200
 of evil and the total presence of himself.

1038
00:41:50,200 --> 00:41:53,720
 And the beauty of this is this day doesn't end.

1039
00:41:53,720 --> 00:41:58,720
 God has invited us into a story where we enjoy him forever.

1040
00:41:58,720 --> 00:41:59,860
 Isn't that amazing?

1041
00:41:59,860 --> 00:42:03,360
 Last story.

1042
00:42:03,360 --> 00:42:08,860
 Last point, God created life to enjoy, not just endure.

1043
00:42:08,860 --> 00:42:11,460
 Now last story.

1044
00:42:11,460 --> 00:42:14,880
 (congregation laughing)

1045
00:42:14,880 --> 00:42:19,800
 When I was sitting with TA at lunch that day,

1046
00:42:19,800 --> 00:42:22,300
 he looked at me and he asked me

1047
00:42:22,300 --> 00:42:24,440
 what I was doing with my life.

1048
00:42:24,440 --> 00:42:25,680
 And I was struck to the core.

1049
00:42:25,680 --> 00:42:27,960
 I didn't know what I was doing with my life.

1050
00:42:27,960 --> 00:42:33,120
 And then he extended an invitation.

1051
00:42:33,120 --> 00:42:36,400
 He said, hey, when you feel like God makes it clear for you

1052
00:42:36,400 --> 00:42:38,040
 what you're supposed to be doing,

1053
00:42:38,040 --> 00:42:40,440
 why don't you give me a call?

1054
00:42:41,420 --> 00:42:44,060
 Because I'd love to bring you on staff here with me.

1055
00:42:44,060 --> 00:42:48,660
 And in that moment, I went from crisis to clarity

1056
00:42:48,660 --> 00:42:53,740
 in a world where I felt so much confusion

1057
00:42:53,740 --> 00:42:55,060
 about what I was supposed to be doing,

1058
00:42:55,060 --> 00:42:57,580
 so much so that I was doing everything instead.

1059
00:42:57,580 --> 00:43:00,460
 In that moment, I felt like I had crystal clarity

1060
00:43:00,460 --> 00:43:02,420
 of what my purpose was.

1061
00:43:02,420 --> 00:43:04,620
 It wasn't just a work in this ministry

1062
00:43:04,620 --> 00:43:09,620
 to sign up for vocational full-time lifelong church work.

1063
00:43:09,740 --> 00:43:12,680
 That's not what I felt clarity of.

1064
00:43:12,680 --> 00:43:16,700
 What I felt clarity of from God is I processed the offer

1065
00:43:16,700 --> 00:43:19,320
 of leaving everything else behind

1066
00:43:19,320 --> 00:43:24,080
 and stepping in to what God was doing through this ministry

1067
00:43:24,080 --> 00:43:25,340
 by way of his gospel.

1068
00:43:25,340 --> 00:43:28,840
 What I felt was purpose.

1069
00:43:28,840 --> 00:43:33,200
 I knew my life is meant to make him known.

1070
00:43:33,200 --> 00:43:35,980
 It's to know him and it's to make him known.

1071
00:43:39,240 --> 00:43:41,920
 That is the same offer on the table for you, friend.

1072
00:43:41,920 --> 00:43:45,720
 You're here and I don't know what your world feels like.

1073
00:43:45,720 --> 00:43:48,320
 Maybe you've entered in the new year and you're pumped,

1074
00:43:48,320 --> 00:43:50,340
 like you're so excited, you've got great goals

1075
00:43:50,340 --> 00:43:52,100
 and you're already checking them down,

1076
00:43:52,100 --> 00:43:54,120
 like every single day on your calendar,

1077
00:43:54,120 --> 00:43:56,620
 you're checking off whatever it is you're trying

1078
00:43:56,620 --> 00:43:59,080
 to stay true to and build the habit of,

1079
00:43:59,080 --> 00:44:01,640
 but others of you, you're not here excited for the new year,

1080
00:44:01,640 --> 00:44:04,400
 you're here and you're concerned about it.

1081
00:44:04,400 --> 00:44:06,100
 Because already three weeks in,

1082
00:44:06,100 --> 00:44:08,280
 like you know the sins of your past,

1083
00:44:08,280 --> 00:44:09,800
 they're already here in the present,

1084
00:44:09,800 --> 00:44:12,600
 they're already walking with you today.

1085
00:44:12,600 --> 00:44:14,700
 And so you're wondering, man, is it already too late?

1086
00:44:14,700 --> 00:44:17,120
 Have I ruined 2026?

1087
00:44:17,120 --> 00:44:19,560
 The truth of the matter is you haven't ruined anything

1088
00:44:19,560 --> 00:44:21,280
 because Christ has fixed everything

1089
00:44:21,280 --> 00:44:23,960
 for those that place their faith in him.

1090
00:44:23,960 --> 00:44:27,120
 You see, Jesus is not indifferent towards you,

1091
00:44:27,120 --> 00:44:28,720
 he is intentional about you.

1092
00:44:28,720 --> 00:44:31,720
 So intentional in fact, that he left heaven, came to earth

1093
00:44:31,720 --> 00:44:34,320
 and he moved with such purpose,

1094
00:44:34,320 --> 00:44:38,200
 such clarity of conviction that he would live the life

1095
00:44:38,200 --> 00:44:39,680
 you could not.

1096
00:44:39,680 --> 00:44:42,120
 And the way that he did it is he didn't just become

1097
00:44:42,120 --> 00:44:44,520
 a human being like us, he actually became the human doing

1098
00:44:44,520 --> 00:44:45,640
 that we cannot do.

1099
00:44:45,640 --> 00:44:48,560
 He did everything perfect in the life he lived.

1100
00:44:48,560 --> 00:44:51,400
 He accomplished all the law and the prophets in a way

1101
00:44:51,400 --> 00:44:54,740
 that led us into right relationship with God.

1102
00:44:54,740 --> 00:44:58,680
 But it isn't just that, what we see is that Christ,

1103
00:44:58,680 --> 00:45:02,560
 he has come to give us life, but also life abundantly

1104
00:45:02,560 --> 00:45:05,000
 because you have been designed not just to enjoy this world,

1105
00:45:05,000 --> 00:45:07,200
 but to enjoy the God of this world.

1106
00:45:07,200 --> 00:45:10,320
 And where he is in his presence is the fullness

1107
00:45:10,320 --> 00:45:11,760
 of that kind of joy.

1108
00:45:11,760 --> 00:45:14,120
 Christ has come to restore you to that.

1109
00:45:14,120 --> 00:45:16,080
 So I don't know where you're at tonight,

1110
00:45:16,080 --> 00:45:18,560
 I don't know how you feel about this year,

1111
00:45:18,560 --> 00:45:21,800
 but here's what I would say, whatever story you're trying

1112
00:45:21,800 --> 00:45:23,960
 to write for the year that's still ahead,

1113
00:45:23,960 --> 00:45:26,480
 Christ, he wants to write a completely different story

1114
00:45:26,480 --> 00:45:28,960
 and I promise you that story will be better.

1115
00:45:28,960 --> 00:45:32,520
 Your purpose is to know God and listen, when you know him,

1116
00:45:32,520 --> 00:45:37,100
 you'll realize there is no one more worth knowing.

1117
00:45:37,100 --> 00:45:40,240
 Let me pray that you would know him.

1118
00:45:40,240 --> 00:45:41,420
 God, thank you.

1119
00:45:41,420 --> 00:45:44,120
 Your word is so good, it's so beautiful.

1120
00:45:44,120 --> 00:45:48,360
 I love that we can just sit here and study it in a way

1121
00:45:48,360 --> 00:45:49,800
 where God, it doesn't just fill up our hearts,

1122
00:45:49,800 --> 00:45:51,320
 it enriches our minds.

1123
00:45:51,320 --> 00:45:55,120
 Like we realize just who you are, how good you are.

1124
00:45:55,120 --> 00:45:58,560
 And so God, when I'm praying right now is that God,

1125
00:45:58,560 --> 00:46:01,200
 he would work by way of your spirit,

1126
00:46:01,920 --> 00:46:06,920
 you would call people to place their faith in you

1127
00:46:06,920 --> 00:46:10,240
 if they have not, to rededicate their lives to you

1128
00:46:10,240 --> 00:46:14,520
 if they have not, and God to go faster and further with you

1129
00:46:14,520 --> 00:46:16,920
 than they may already be going.

1130
00:46:16,920 --> 00:46:19,720
 This is a truth, God, that doesn't just apply to some of us,

1131
00:46:19,720 --> 00:46:21,840
 this is a truth, God, that applies to all of us.

1132
00:46:21,840 --> 00:46:24,280
 And so God, I'm praying what my friend Natalie prayed

1133
00:46:24,280 --> 00:46:26,840
 earlier, that God, you would work in a way

1134
00:46:26,840 --> 00:46:29,840
 that touches every single soul.

1135
00:46:29,840 --> 00:46:32,040
 Oh God, you can do that.

1136
00:46:32,040 --> 00:46:35,120
 God, you can do it.

1137
00:46:35,120 --> 00:46:36,740
 And so I'm praying for it, God.

1138
00:46:36,740 --> 00:46:40,040
 I am entering this year expectant,

1139
00:46:40,040 --> 00:46:42,280
 not just because God, I want all the fruit

1140
00:46:42,280 --> 00:46:44,440
 of a really awesome year, but because God,

1141
00:46:44,440 --> 00:46:49,440
 I want the one who makes all things awesome, I want you.

1142
00:46:49,440 --> 00:46:52,280
 And so God, come to us.

1143
00:46:52,280 --> 00:46:53,920
 Right now, I would invite you, man,

1144
00:46:53,920 --> 00:46:58,080
 would you just invite God to invade your space,

1145
00:46:58,080 --> 00:47:02,000
 to enter into your mind, to move in your heart,

1146
00:47:02,000 --> 00:47:04,640
 to stir what need be awakened awake.

1147
00:47:04,640 --> 00:47:08,440
 There is a response in the room for us all,

1148
00:47:08,440 --> 00:47:12,160
 so let us respond, not because I'm asking you to,

1149
00:47:12,160 --> 00:47:14,600
 but because he is worthy of it.

1150
00:47:14,600 --> 00:47:16,800
 What a God we have.

1151
00:47:16,800 --> 00:47:18,680
 What a God you are.

1152
00:47:18,680 --> 00:47:22,080
 There is no one higher, there is no one greater,

1153
00:47:22,080 --> 00:47:24,280
 there is no one more worthy.

1154
00:47:24,280 --> 00:47:28,040
 And so God, it is to you that we declare this year,

1155
00:47:28,040 --> 00:47:32,760
 this year from this night, it is yours.

1156
00:47:32,760 --> 00:47:37,400
 King Jesus, we follow you, we follow no one else.

1157
00:47:37,400 --> 00:47:42,400
 We want your spirit, we want the life you have to give.

1158
00:47:42,400 --> 00:47:44,760
 So won't you come and give it to us right now,

1159
00:47:44,760 --> 00:47:47,640
 we pray in Christ's name, amen.

